{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> στάζω</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Hipponax Iambographus 57, etc.\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> στάξω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Jer.49(42).18 \">LXX</a>], <i>Aeolic dialect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> στάξοισι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 9.63 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Doric dialect</i> <i>1st pers.</i> <i>plural</i> σταξεῦμες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 18.46 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἔσταξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 1355 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Epic dialect</i> στάξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.39, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 10.82 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, (ἐν-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 2.179: \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<i>aorist 1</i> ἐστάχθην (ἐπ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἑλκῶν” 21: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist 2</i> ἐστάγην (ἐπ-, ἐν-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.19, 2.35: \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>drop, let fall</b> or <b>shed drop by drop</b>, [Θέτις] Πατρόκλῳ.. νέκταρ στάξε κατὰ ῥινῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.39, compare 348, 354 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; σπέρμα θνατὸν ματρὶ τεᾷ στάξεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 10.81; ἐξ ὀμμάτων σ. αἷμα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 1058; ἱδρῶτα σώματος ἄπο 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 620 (troch.), compare “Tr.” 1199; βότρυν [prev. author] “Ph.” 230 (Lyric poetry); ὕδωρ σ. πέτρα [prev. author] “Hipp.” 122 (Lyric poetry)\